OL,3,CSir Keir Starmer to update House of
OL,4,CCommons on latest Mandelson revelations
OL,6,FA crunch week for Sir Keir Starmer is
OL,7,Fset to continue on Monday as he
OL,8,Fupdates the House of Commons on the
OL,9,Flatest revelations about Lord
OL,10,FMandelson's appointment.
OL,12,FNo 10 on Friday night released a
OL,13,Freadout of a meeting between the Prime
OL,14,FMinister and senior civil servants
OL,15,Fthat appeared to corroborate that Sir
OL,16,FKeir only found out on Tuesday that
OL,17,FLord Mandelson was cleared for his
OL,18,Frole as Britain's representative in
OL,19,FWashington against the advice of
OL,20,Fsecurity officials.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1776690659
OL,3,CSir Keir Starmer to update House of
OL,4,CCommons on latest Mandelson revelations
OL,6,FThe Foreign Office has been blamed for
OL,7,Fclearing the peer in January 2025 to
OL,8,Fbegin as US ambassador, despite him
OL,9,Ffailing a secure vetting process.
OL,11,FThe Prime Minister has said he was
OL,12,F"absolutely furious", and described
OL,13,Fthe failure to inform him as
OL,14,F"staggering".
OL,16,FSir Olly Robbins, who was only weeks
OL,17,Finto his job as Foreign Office
OL,18,Fpermanent secretary at the time, was
OL,19,Fsacked on Thursday as he had lost the
OL,20,Fconfidence of Sir Keir and Foreign
OL,21,FSecretary Yvette Cooper.
OL,26,@tD@AOUtD@TO]vD@AOUvD@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1776690659
OL,3,CSir Keir Starmer to update House of
OL,4,CCommons on latest Mandelson revelations
OL,6,FHe is expected to speak to the Foreign
OL,7,FAffairs Committee as early as next
OL,8,FTuesday, a day after Sir Keir will
OL,9,Fupdate the Commons on the latest
OL,10,Ftwists in the saga.
OL,12,FThe committee on Saturday published
OL,13,Fcorrespondence showing that Ms Cooper
OL,14,Fhad asked the FCDO to conduct a "full
OL,15,Freview" of all the information the
OL,16,Fdepartment had provided to the
OL,17,Fcommittee.
OL,26,@vD@aOUwD@GO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1776690659
OL,3,CSir Keir Starmer to update House of
OL,4,CCommons on latest Mandelson revelations
OL,6,FLord Simon McDonald, permanent
OL,7,Fsecretary at the Foreign Office from
OL,8,F2015-2020, told BBC Radio 4's Today
OL,9,Fprogramme that Sir Olly was "thrown
OL,10,Funder the bus" and that Number 10
OL,11,F"wanted a scalp and they wanted it
OL,12,Fquickly".
OL,14,FThe Guardian reported on Friday that
OL,15,FAntonia Romeo, the head of the civil
OL,16,Fservice, and Cabinet Office permanent
OL,17,Fsecretary Catherine Little, had found
OL,18,Fout before the Prime Minister about
OL,19,FLord Mandelson's failure to gain
OL,20,Fvetting.
OL,26,@qD@]OUrD@NO]sD@AOUtD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1776690659
OL,3,CSir Keir Starmer to update House of
OL,4,CCommons on latest Mandelson revelations
OL,6,FThe readout of Tuesday's meeting gave
OL,7,Fcredence to this, as Ms Little had
OL,8,Freceived information about the vetting
OL,9,Fas part of the process to release
OL,10,Ffiles related to Lord Mandelson's
OL,11,Fappointment, which MPs voted for in
OL,12,FFebruary.
OL,14,F"On reviewing the file she had
OL,15,Ftherefore learned that the
OL,16,Frecommendation from the vetting
OL,17,Fofficer had been that DV (Developed
OL,18,FVetting) should not be granted to
OL,19,FPeter Mandelson," the readout said.
OL,26,@vD@AOU{D@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1776690659
OL,3,CSir Keir Starmer to update House of
OL,4,CCommons on latest Mandelson revelations
OL,6,FThe Cabinet Office denied that this
OL,7,Fmeant the senior civil servant had sat
OL,8,Fon the details, while a Government
OL,9,Fsource said: "Cat has been the one
OL,10,Fdoggedly fighting Olly Robbins to get
OL,11,Fthe documents out of his clutches and
OL,12,Finto the public domain.
OL,14,F"This is a laughable attempt to shift
OL,15,Fblame from the actual person who kept
OL,16,Fthe PM in the dark."
OL,26,@qD@NOUvD@AOUxD@TO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
