PN,31207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1776690659
OL,3,CSir Keir Starmer to update House of
OL,4,CCommons on latest Mandelson revelations
OL,6,FThe leaders of the major opposition
OL,7,Fparties have all called for Sir Keir
OL,8,Fto resign over the latest revelations,
OL,9,Fwith Kemi Badenoch claiming the Prime
OL,10,FMinister had misled Parliament and the
OL,11,Fpublic.
OL,13,FScotland's First Minister John Swinney
OL,14,Fsaid it was the Prime Minister's
OL,15,F"incompetence" that was "staggering".
OL,17,FLiberal Democrat leader Sir Ed Davey
OL,18,Fsaid that Sir Keir must publish the
OL,19,Fadvice he received on Lord Mandelson's
OL,20,Fappointment.
OL,26,@wD@AOUwD@NO]wD@YOUwD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
